{
  "title": "Starter packs",
  "tagline": "One core design system, sixteen brand personalities.",
  "intro": "A pack is not a template. It is a tiny Brand — a couple of colors, a font pairing, a rounding feel — that the pure `applyBrand` function turns into a complete, WCAG-checked theme. Every card below is derived live at build time from the brand shown beneath it: same components, same spacing, same accessibility rules. Only the personality changes.",
  "principles": [
    "Don't design 20 design systems — design 1 core system and 20 brand personalities.",
    "Packs differ only in colors, typography, radius, shadow and mood — never in layout logic, component behavior or API.",
    "Every first-party pack passes the WCAG 2.2 AA contrast gate through applyBrand — accessibility is derived, not decorated.",
    "Generic first (the seven packs that fit most sites), then broad industries — no hyper-niche one-offs.",
    "Taste bar: Modern, Clean, Professional, Premium, Timeless. No glassmorphism, neumorphism or brutalism defaults."
  ],
  "curationNote": "These mirror the starter packs Flexa Builder ships; the curation SSOT is design-pack-philosophy.md.",
  "groups": [
